PART 5: EXHAUSTIVE n=5 WITH DIRECTED 5-CYCLES AS SEPARATE NODES
======================================================================

n=5 exhaustive (1024 tournaments):
  H = I(2) matches (vertex-set method): 840/1024
  H = I(2) matches (directed-cycle method): 1024/1024
  I(-1) max (directed-cycle): 1
  I(-1) > 1 violations (directed-cycle): 0

======================================================================
PART 6: THE REAL FORMULA — MAYBE NOT INDEPENDENCE POLYNOMIAL?
======================================================================

The OCF formula is: H(T) = Σ_{S independent in Ω(T)} 2^|S|
This IS the independence polynomial at x=2.

But WAIT: the original OCF from THM-070 says:
H = I(Ω(T), 2)
And this was VERIFIED at small n.

Let me check if the verification used 3-cycles only!

Using ONLY 3-cycles at n=5: 480/1024 match H=I(2)

If this is <100%, then 3-cycles alone don't suffice.
If 100%, then the OCF might only need 3-cycles!
